author: J
text: .Mr. Anchorman, when you ask a question have Patience  for the respondents to complete the answer. I know your style of interview and this kind of method appeals only to some few groups.It looks like you are a wannabe Mr. Rishi Dhamala.Please this style of interviewing is copied from some obsolete Indian news channel and  you get jerky when someone talks about India. This does not work for a long time. I just had a software calculate how much the anchor is speaking vs. The other two. The anchors speech takes almost 47% of the interview time. And the rest is divided among the other two.Now what is the point?You've got the gift of the gab, we expect you to use it more responsibly. Otherwise most of the interviews  a lot of people find you irritating and when I say a lot trust me it's a lot, but not me. I just want quality improved in a Nepalese media.If you really want to master this style learn from BBC Hardtalk.
